            '<div id="attachment_232565" style="width: 2010px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-232565" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-232565 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2.jpg" alt="A bird nest made of spikes and branches in a tree" width="2000" height="1400" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-640x448.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-960x672.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-1536x1075.jpg 1536w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-624x437.jpg 624w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-150x105.jpg 150w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-640x448@2x.jpg 1280w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-2-960x672@2x.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><p id="caption-attachment-232565" class="wp-caption-text">All images courtesy of Denisea</p></div>\n<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hostile_architecture" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hostile architecture</a> is a design strategy that restricts access to public space. Spikes protruding from doorways, fences under stairs, and curved benches that require the user to stabilize themselves with their feet are examples of the inhumane practice that deters unhoused, poor, and young people from gathering in urban areas. The approach also applies to non-human species, and birds are primary targets—a few years back, a Bristol tree was even spotted with <a href="https://www.cnn.com/style/article/new-dean-harvey-james-furzer-hostile-architecture-debate/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">spines lining its branches</a>.</p>\n<p>But as researchers from Naturalis Biodiversity Center and the Natural History Museum Rotterdam have discovered, our feathered friends have more ingenuity than architects thought. <a href="https://www.hetnatuurhistorisch.nl/fileadmin/user_upload/documents-nmr/Publicaties/Deinsea/Deinsea_21/Deinsea_21_17_25_2023_Hiemstra_et_al.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A paper</a> published this month in <em>Deinsea</em> highlights several examples of magpies and carrion crows building nests with strips of anti-bird spikes in both Rotterdam and Antwerp. Magpies are particularly enterprising and use pointed edges for their original purpose: many have lined the roofs of their homes with the spikes to deter predators from snatching eggs.</p>\n<p>Adhesive residue also suggests that the birds ripped the unwelcoming materials from their original places and combined them with twigs, netting, and other findings. This comes after <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/jul/05/chick-flick-cockatoo-gives-anti-nesting-spikes-the-bird-in-viral-video" target="_blank" rel="noopener">several sightings</a> of cockatoos tearing the strips from buildings and is part of a long history of avians using human-made material like knitting needles and <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/132029a0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">barbed wire</a> for their nests.  &#8220;It&#8217;s actually like a joke,&#8221; biologist Auke-Florian Hiemstra said about the findings. &#8220;Even for me as a nest researcher, these are the craziest bird nests I&#8217;ve ever seen.&#8221;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-232566 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3.jpg" alt="A bird nest made of spikes and branches in a tree" width="2000" height="1253" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-640x401.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-960x601.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-1536x962.jpg 1536w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-624x391.jpg 624w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-150x94.jpg 150w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-640x401@2x.jpg 1280w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-3-960x601@2x.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p>\n<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-232567 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4.jpg" alt="A bird nest made of spikes and branches in a tree" width="2000" height="1250" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4.jpg 2000w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-640x400.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-960x600.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-1536x960.jpg 1536w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-624x390.jpg 624w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-150x94.jpg 150w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-640x400@2x.jpg 1280w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-4-960x600@2x.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p>\n<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-232564 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1.jpg" alt="A bird nest made of spikes and branches on a white backdrop" width="1450" height="1450" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1.jpg 1450w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-640x640.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-960x960.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-624x624.jpg 624w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-50x50.jpg 50w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-96x96.jpg 96w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-640x640@2x.jpg 1280w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-1-150x150@2x.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1450px) 100vw, 1450px" /></p>\n<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-232568 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5.jpg" alt="A bird nest made of spikes and branches on a white backdrop" width="1240" height="1171" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5.jpg 1240w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5-640x604.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5-960x907.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5-624x589.jpg 624w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/birds-5-150x142.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>\n<p>Do stories and artists like this matter to you? Become a <a href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/members">Colossal Member</a> today and support independent arts publishing for as little as $5 per month. The article <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2023/07/crows-magpies-spike-nests/">Crows and Magpies Are Building Nests with Anti-Bird Spikes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com">Colossal</a>.</p>',
