        '<p>&#8220;There is something mysterious and magical about masks,&#8221; says <a href="https://www.instagram.com/joao_charrua/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">João Charrua</a>. &#8220;A mask intrinsically carries an energy with which we identify in some way. They are like portals to our imagination.&#8221; Through carefully planned and meticulous folds, the Portugal-based artist models human faces from single sheets of paper, crafting delicate noses, expressive brows, and angular jawlines.<br />\nCharrua began exploring origami around 13 years ago, when he was looking for a pastime to share with his daughter. <span class="more"><a href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2023/07/joao-charrua-origami-portraits/">More</a></span></p>\n<p>Do stories and artists like this matter to you? Become a <a href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/members">Colossal Member</a> today and support independent arts publishing for as little as $5 per month. The article <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2023/07/joao-charrua-origami-portraits/">João Charrua Intricately Folds Single Pieces of Paper to Reveal Precisely Rendered Portraits</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com">Colossal</a>.</p>',
