      summary:
        '<p> </p><p dir="ltr">Writer-director Christopher McQuarrie revealed that the conclusion of Mission: Impossible - Dead Reckoning Part One was a topic of great concern for star Tom Cruise during production. According to McQuarrie in a recent interview with <a href="https://www.gamesradar.com/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-ending-choice-christopher-mcquarrie-interview/">Total Film magazine</a>, Cruise literally lost sleep over it, upset over the possibility of a cliffhanger ending.</p><p dir="ltr">"Where we ended the movie was always where we were going to end it," McQuarrie said. "How we ended the movie was a big, big mystery for us. It kept Tom awake at night throughout production. He would come in all the time and say, \'This can\'t be a cliffhanger, it\'s got to be satisfying.\' The audience has to feel a sense of completion."</p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/tom-cruise-refused-to-let-mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-1-end-on-a-cliffhanger/1100-6516006/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f/">Continue Reading at GameSpot</a>',
